while I take my stuff upstairs?

323
00:44:54.297 --> 00:44:55.422
Of course.

324
00:45:16.403 --> 00:45:19.613
I'm putting the name of a girl
in my class who makes me sick.

325
00:45:22.200 --> 00:45:25.703
When things get hot,
she'll take the heat.

326
00:45:43.596 --> 00:45:45.389
There, finished.

327
00:45:45.515 --> 00:45:48.935
- How old are you?
- Eighteen.

328
00:45:49.686 --> 00:45:51.270
Eighteen?

329
00:45:51.396 --> 00:45:53.564
Wanna see my license?

330
00:45:53.690 --> 00:45:57.944
No. You just look a little. . .younger.

331
00:45:58.862 --> 00:46:00.279
Thanks.

332
00:46:07.620 --> 00:46:11.165
Leon, I want you to teach me
how to be like you.

333
00:46:11.291 --> 00:46:14.085
I wanna be strong like you,
smart like you.

334
00:46:14.211 --> 00:46:16.837
- Mathilda. . .
- I know I'm not strong enough yet.

335
00:46:18.215 --> 00:46:22.259
But I could learn the basics, the theory.

336
00:46:22.385 --> 00:46:25.554
What do you think?
Just the theory.

337
00:46:27.099 --> 00:46:32.644
I need this, Leon. I need time
to get my head together.

338
00:46:32.770 --> 00:46:34.938
Yeah. And I need. . .

339
00:46:41.404 --> 00:46:42.738
. . .a drink.

340
00:46:43.990 --> 00:46:45.824
Don't move. I'll go get one.

341
00:46:53.082 --> 00:46:54.416
Salute.

342
00:47:10.933 --> 00:47:14.395
You know, when you told me
to get this baby out for you,

343
00:47:14.521 --> 00:47:16.730
I thought my hearing's going.

344
00:47:16.856 --> 00:47:21.652
I says to myself, "Leon's a pro.
Nobody uses that, except beginners."

345
00:47:21.778 --> 00:47:23.487
I like to stay in shape.

346
00:47:23.613 --> 00:47:25.155
Sure.

347
00:47:26.198 --> 00:47:28.241
Always stay on top.

348
00:47:28.368 --> 00:47:31.244
It's like me. I gotta know
where everything is all the time.

349
00:47:31.371 --> 00:47:34.456
That's why I never leave this place
except to go from here to there.

350
00:47:37.877 --> 00:47:40.712
Change ain't good, Leon. You know?

351
00:47:44.801 --> 00:47:46.217
Yeah.

352
00:47:51.808 --> 00:47:53.308
Check it.

353
00:47:55.061 --> 00:47:57.437
- Make sure it's the right thing.
- I trust you.

354
00:47:57.564 --> 00:47:59.773
One thing's got nothing
to do with the other.

355
00:47:59.899 --> 00:48:02.067
Remember that, Leon.

356
00:48:02.193 --> 00:48:03.610
I will.

357
00:48:19.001 --> 00:48:22.170
The rifle is the first weapon
you learn how to use,

358
00:48:22.296 --> 00:48:25.966
because it lets you keep
your distance from the client.

359
00:48:26.092 --> 00:48:30.053
The closer you get to being a pro,
the closer you can get to the client.

360
00:48:31.555 --> 00:48:35.016
The knife, for example,
is the last thing you learn.

361
00:48:36.393 --> 00:48:39.020
- OK?
- OK.

362
00:48:40.857 --> 00:48:42.107
Position.

363
00:49:03.921 --> 00:49:05.338
No.

364
00:49:06.298 --> 00:49:10.135
Never take it off until the last minute,
it reflects light.

365
00:49:10.261 --> 00:49:13.179
They can see you coming
from a mile away.

366
00:49:13.305 --> 00:49:19.519
And always dress down,
never brighter than the floor. OK?

367
00:49:20.479 --> 00:49:21.897
OK.

368
00:49:23.482 --> 00:49:26.609
Let's practice now.
It's the best way to learn.

369
00:49:27.611 --> 00:49:29.737
Who should I hit?

370
00:49:29.863 --> 00:49:31.531
Whoever.

371
00:49:38.414 --> 00:49:40.623
I'll be with you in a second,
give me a few minutes.

372
00:49:40.749 --> 00:49:44.794
You guys in the suits get lost.
I don't want to see you, all right?

373
00:49:44.920 --> 00:49:46.879
It has to look natural.

374
00:49:56.473 --> 00:49:58.349
No women, no kids, right?

375
00:49:58.475 --> 00:49:59.934
Right.

376
00:50:07.193 --> 00:50:09.527
The jogger in the yellow and orange?

377
00:50:09.653 --> 00:50:11.070
OK.

378
00:50:14.241 --> 00:50:15.741
Keep calm.

379
00:50:19.996 --> 00:50:22.290
Don't take your eyes off him.

380
00:50:23.625 --> 00:50:25.335
Breathe easy.

381
00:50:27.045 --> 00:50:28.588
Watch his movement.

382
00:50:31.174 --> 00:50:33.426
Pretend you're running with him.

383
00:50:37.431 --> 00:50:39.849
Try to feel his next movement.

384
00:50:41.477 --> 00:50:44.061
Take a deep breath, hold it.

385
00:50:53.489 --> 00:50:54.655
Now.

386
00:50:56.700 --> 00:50:59.952
- I'm all right. I'm fine. I'm fine.
- Get down!

387
00:51:00.704 --> 00:51:02.788
One shot. Not bad, huh?

388
00:51:07.461 --> 00:51:10.045
Can we try with real bullets now?

389
00:51:10.547 --> 00:51:12.465
Not today. Let's pack up.

390
00:51:21.474 --> 00:51:23.392
Continue like that.

391
00:51:23.977 --> 00:51:25.978
Here, after. . .

392
00:52:06.436 --> 00:52:07.728
No thanks.

393
00:52:07.854 --> 00:52:09.563
No discussion.

394
00:52:50.771 --> 00:52:52.564
"It seemed. . .

395
00:52:53.816 --> 00:52:55.942
". . .to Socrates. . ."

396
00:52:58.654 --> 00:53:01.656
To So-cra-tes. . .

397
00:53:03.784 --> 00:53:05.410
I'll do it.

398
00:53:19.592 --> 00:53:21.760
Leon, all we do is work.

399
00:53:22.303 --> 00:53:25.472
We need a break. Let's play a game.

400
00:53:25.598 --> 00:53:27.141
What kind of game?

401
00:53:27.267 --> 00:53:29.100
I have this great game.

402
00:53:29.227 --> 00:53:31.311
It makes you think
and it helps your memory.

403
00:53:31.437 --> 00:53:33.104
It's exactly what you need.

404
00:53:35.941 --> 00:53:37.442
OK.

405
00:53:58.130 --> 00:54:00.799
- OK. Who is it?
- I don't know.

406
00:54:21.236 --> 00:54:22.862
I don't know.

407
00:54:32.414 --> 00:54:34.248
Moustache. . .

408
00:54:37.002 --> 00:54:38.169
No.

409
00:54:46.220 --> 00:54:48.722
Gene Kelly?

410
00:54:48.848 --> 00:54:50.139
Good.

411
00:54:50.683 --> 00:54:52.475
Your turn now.

412
00:54:58.691 --> 00:55:00.316
OK, pilgrim.

413
00:55:04.113 --> 00:55:06.405
Clint Eastwood?

414
00:55:12.287 --> 00:55:13.830
I don't know, I give up.

415
00:55:15.415 --> 00:55:16.958
John Wayne.

416
00:55:17.793 --> 00:55:20.419
I was just about to say that, I swear.

417
00:55:20.545 --> 00:55:23.672
It's amazing, Leon, really, brilliant.

418
00:55:26.260 --> 00:55:27.718
Amazing.

419
00:55:42.985 --> 00:55:45.819
- You love your plant, don't you?
- It's my best friend.

420
00:55:47.489 --> 00:55:50.074
Always happy. No questions.

421
00:55:52.619 --> 00:55:54.620
And it's like me, you see?

422
00:55:55.956 --> 00:55:57.748
No roots.

423
00:55:57.874 --> 00:56:01.627
If you really love it, you should plant it
in the park so it can have roots.

424
00:56:05.715 --> 00:56:09.510
I'm the one you should be watering
if you want me to grow.

425
00:56:10.929 --> 00:56:13.139
You're right.

426
00:56:18.645 --> 00:56:21.230
- No.
- Yes, yes, yes!

427
00:56:40.125 --> 00:56:43.502
They gotta be jumping out of the plate,
they gotta be alive.

428
00:56:52.554 --> 00:56:54.847
It's been a long time, Leon.

429
00:57:00.895 --> 00:57:02.646
I missed you.

430
00:57:02.772 --> 00:57:05.941
And you missed some nice jobs, too.

431
00:57:06.067 --> 00:57:08.694
- Been training.
- Training's good.

432
00:57:10.364 --> 00:57:14.116
But don't overdo it. You know training
don't pay as good as working, Leon.

433
00:57:14.242 --> 00:57:15.993
Tony. . .

434
00:57:18.830 --> 00:57:23.166
All the money I make. . .
that you keep for me.

435
00:57:23.292 --> 00:57:25.168
You need some money?

436
00:57:25.294 --> 00:57:26.879
No. Just curious.

437
00:57:27.005 --> 00:57:28.964
Because I've been working a long time

438
00:57:29.090 --> 00:57:31.800
and I haven't done anything
with my money. . .

439
00:57:34.888 --> 00:57:37.556
I thought maybe some day I could. . .

440
00:57:39.350 --> 00:57:40.559
. . .use it.

441
00:57:42.020 --> 00:57:44.354
You met a woman?

442
00:57:52.739 --> 00:57:55.407
Leon, you gotta be careful
with women.

443
00:57:55.534 --> 00:57:59.745
Remember when you arrived in
this country, Leon, when I took you in?

444
00:57:59.871 --> 00:58:02.205
You were still wet
behind the fucking ears,

445
00:58:02.331 --> 00:58:05.208
and already you were in deep shit
because of a woman.

446
00:58:05.334 --> 00:58:06.960
Don't forget that, Leon.

447
00:58:07.086 --> 00:58:09.254
Wish I could, sometimes.

448
00:58:12.884 --> 00:58:15.093
You know, about my money.

449
00:58:15.219 --> 00:58:20.390
Maybe I. . .
Maybe I could give. . .a little. . .

450
00:58:23.394 --> 00:58:25.520
. . .to someone.

451
00:58:25.647 --> 00:58:28.732
You know, to help out.

452
00:58:28.858 --> 00:58:35.322
Hey, it's your money, I mean,
I'm just holding it for you, like a bank.

453
00:58:35.448 --> 00:58:37.365
Except, you know, better than a bank,

454
00:58:37.491 --> 00:58:40.077
because banks are always
getting knocked off.

455
00:58:40.203 --> 00:58:42.120
And no one knocks off old Tony.

456
00:58:42.246 --> 00:58:44.790
And besides, with a bank,

457
00:58:44.916 --> 00:58:48.251
there's always tons of forms
to be filled and all that shit.

458
00:58:48.377 --> 00:58:51.213
But old Tony, nothing to read,
nothing to write.

459
00:58:52.381 --> 00:58:54.341
It's all in his head.

460
00:58:54.467 --> 00:58:56.634
I know how to read now.

461
00:58:58.721 --> 00:59:01.348
That's good, Leon.

462
00:59:01.474 --> 00:59:02.765
Good.

463
00:59:04.352 --> 00:59:05.853
Your money's here.

464
00:59:05.979 --> 00:59:09.231
Whenever you want it,
you just ask me, OK?

465
00:59:09.357 --> 00:59:11.316
- Here's a grand.
- It's OK. I don't need it.

466
00:59:11.442 --> 00:59:15.237
Come on, come on, take it.
Have some fun. Go ahead. Take it.

467
00:59:15.363 --> 00:59:17.030
Thank you.

468
00:59:17.156 --> 00:59:18.615
All right.

469
00:59:19.492 --> 00:59:23.120
Now let's talk business.
Don't move, I'll go get the file.

470
00:59:24.747 --> 00:59:27.957
Manolo, a glass of milk
for my friend Leon here!

471
00:59:52.108 --> 00:59:54.359
Listen, Mathilda, you gotta be careful.

472
00:59:54.485 --> 00:59:57.654
You can't just speak
to any guy off the street.

473
00:59:58.406 --> 01:00:01.158
Leon, get a grip.
What's the big fucking deal?

474
01:00:01.284 --> 01:00:04.411
I was just smoking a butt
while I was waiting.

475
01:00:05.829 --> 01:00:07.830
I want you to stop cursing.

476
01:00:07.956 --> 01:00:10.333
You can't talk to people
like that all the time.

477
01:00:10.459 --> 01:00:13.420
I want you to make
an effort to talk nice.

478
01:00:15.130 --> 01:00:16.464
OK.

479
01:00:18.175 --> 01:00:21.052
And I want you to stop smoking.
It will kill you.

480
01:00:23.472 --> 01:00:24.806
OK.

481
01:00:28.018 --> 01:00:30.978
Stay away from him,
he looks like a weirdo.

482
01:00:33.316 --> 01:00:34.566
OK.

483
01:00:35.984 --> 01:00:39.404
I'll be out in five minutes,
stand where I can see you.

484
01:00:41.031 --> 01:00:42.239
OK.

485
01:00:53.168 --> 01:00:56.463
Leon, I think I'm kind of falling
in love with you.

486
01:01:00.425 --> 01:01:03.219
It's the first time for me, you know?

487
01:01:03.721 --> 01:01:07.223
How do you know it's love
if you've never been in love before?

488
01:01:07.349 --> 01:01:09.183
Cos I feel it.

489
01:01:10.644 --> 01:01:12.436
Where?

490
01:01:15.065 --> 01:01:16.858
In my stomach.

491
01:01:19.737 --> 01:01:21.445
It's all warm.

492
01:01:23.448 --> 01:01:28.077
I always had a knot there,
and now. . .it's gone.

493
01:01:31.414 --> 01:01:36.418
Mathilda, I'm glad you don't have
a stomach ache anymore.

494
01:01:36.544 --> 01:01:39.130
I don't think that means anything.

495
01:01:39.256 --> 01:01:42.591
I'm late for work.
I hate being late for work.

496
01:02:27.179 --> 01:02:29.638
Hey, how's the practicing going?

497
01:02:59.627 --> 01:03:04.506
- How are we today, Miss?
- A little sick of practicing.

498
01:03:04.632 --> 01:03:06.675
I understand.

499
01:03:06.801 --> 01:03:10.596
But you're doing all right.
I haven't received any complaints at all.

500
01:03:10.722 --> 01:03:14.933
Well, I put a cloth over
the strings to lessen the noise.

501
01:03:15.059 --> 01:03:17.603
Oh? Oh, that's very smart!

502
01:03:17.729 --> 01:03:20.731
- Not everyone loves music.
- I know.

503
01:03:22.567 --> 01:03:25.861
What exactly does your father do?

504
01:03:25.987 --> 01:03:29.323
- Well, he's a composer.
- Ah, that's wonderful.

505
01:03:30.492 --> 01:03:32.659
Except he's not really my father.

506
01:03:38.916 --> 01:03:40.334
He's my lover.

507
01:03:44.506 --> 01:03:46.632
